parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel, including the speedometer, tachometer, and temperature gauges, can lead to accidents or near-misses due to the driver's inability to monitor the vehicle's speed and performance.
symptoms: Speedometer and tachometer lights and backlights fail
making it difficult or impossible to read the gauges
especially at night; temperature gauge fails to move or indicate overheating; lack of warning lights or indicators for engine problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and axle components can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience sudden acceleration or deceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.

especially on hills; transmission slips or hesitates; gear shift locks or becomes stuck; loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system and piston rings can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or complete failure, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
